## WHAT THIS DEPARTMENT IS

D.S.S is the department that investigates the nature of reality using the full scope of human knowledge — including knowledge systems that predate, operate outside of, or have been suppressed by the institutional science that emerged from Western Europe in the last four centuries.

The premise is not that mainstream science is wrong about everything. The premise is that:

1. Science is a method — observation, hypothesis, testing, revision. That method is sound.
2. Scientific institutions are social structures — subject to funding pressures, ideological capture, paradigm conservatism, and in some cases deliberate suppression.
3. Human beings produced sophisticated knowledge of the natural world for tens of thousands of years before European academic institutions existed — and that knowledge deserves serious investigation on its own terms.
4. Some of the most significant scientific questions — the nature of consciousness, the structure of the cosmos, the mechanisms of biological life — remain genuinely open.

D.S.S investigates all of this. It applies the D.R.D source tier standard rigorously — not to protect mainstream consensus, but to distinguish what is actually known from what is claimed, speculated, or fabricated across all frameworks.

