## THE D.R.D STANDARD IN D.S.S

Every claim investigated in D.S.S is tiered:

```
TIER 1 — Primary sources
Ancient texts, archaeological evidence, peer-reviewed research
by credentialed experts with no major conflicts of interest

TIER 2 — Credentialed academic work outside mainstream
Scholars with genuine academic credentials whose work
challenges paradigms — evaluated by quality of evidence

TIER 3 — Serious independent researchers
Non-credentialed researchers with documented methodology,
primary source engagement, and transparent reasoning

TIER 4 — Secondary claims
Claims that cannot be traced to primary sources
or that have no identified origin — used for framing only

TIER 5 — Unsourced assertion
Claims with no traceable origin, no methodology,
no primary source — not used as factual foundation
```

The goal of D.S.S is not to replace mainstream orthodoxy with an alternative orthodoxy. It is to build a genuinely strong knowledge base — one that can identify what is actually known, what is plausibly hypothesized, and what remains open — across the full scope of human knowledge production.

